00:13:38,180 --> 00:13:39,610
She wants me in a cage!

279
00:13:39,610 --> 00:13:40,443
And that's where I am.

280
00:13:40,443 --> 00:13:42,560
I swear, I feel like I got to bust out or die.

281
00:13:42,560 --> 00:13:44,740
You got a life who lives for you, pal.

282
00:13:44,740 --> 00:13:45,573
You got it great!

283
00:13:45,573 --> 00:13:49,088
I mean, people never appreciate it when they got it great.

284
00:13:49,088 --> 00:13:51,755
(phone ringing)

285
00:13:52,738 --> 00:13:53,770
Hello?

286
00:13:53,770 --> 00:13:55,550
Hello, cowboy.

287
00:13:55,550 --> 00:13:56,383
Dave?

288
00:13:58,090 --> 00:13:59,290
I've been thinking about you.

289
00:13:59,290 --> 00:14:00,590
Where are you?

290
00:14:00,590 --> 00:14:02,780
Oh, I'm sorry, you probably can't tell me that.

291
00:14:02,780 --> 00:14:04,850
Right, sorry.

292
00:14:04,850 --> 00:14:07,740
Well, I didn't expect to hear from you.

293
00:14:07,740 --> 00:14:10,210
I didn't expect it either to be honest with you, but

294
00:14:11,440 --> 00:14:13,040
I can't stop thinking about you.

295
00:14:14,700 --> 00:14:17,727
Well what are we going to do about that?

296
00:14:17,727 --> 00:14:19,480
We're going to have me come there.

297
00:14:19,480 --> 00:14:20,830
I just have to work it out.

298
00:14:21,750 --> 00:14:22,900
But I will work it out.

299
00:14:24,020 --> 00:14:26,250
It's a two week course underwater demolitions.

300
00:14:26,250 --> 00:14:28,197
I think you'd be able to teach them a thing or two.

301
00:14:28,197 --> 00:14:29,880
Well there'd be instructors there from Russia,

302
00:14:29,880 --> 00:14:31,000
China for the first time.

303
00:14:31,000 --> 00:14:32,058
Could be invaluable.

304
00:14:32,058 --> 00:14:32,891
All right, well,

305
00:14:32,891 --> 00:14:35,440
I've never had reason to question your judgment before.

306
00:14:35,440 --> 00:14:38,090
If it's useful to you, make your arrangements and go.

307
00:14:38,992 --> 00:14:41,575
(gentle music)

308
00:15:15,510 --> 00:15:16,613
This feels right.

309
00:15:18,476 --> 00:15:19,953
We've been together forever.

310
00:15:23,855 --> 00:15:24,782
So you're here.

311
00:15:24,782 --> 00:15:26,387
Yeah.

312
00:15:26,387 --> 00:15:27,669
What does that mean?

313
00:15:27,669 --> 00:15:28,919
I'm not sure.

314
00:15:30,888 --> 00:15:32,583
It's something we're going to have to find out.

315
00:15:41,950 --> 00:15:43,390
You know, this is my birthday.

316
00:15:43,390 --> 00:15:45,000
Someone's supposed to be cooking for me.

317
00:15:45,000 --> 00:15:45,940
Oh, don't let him kid you.

318
00:15:45,940 --> 00:15:48,760
He'd stab anybody who touched his precious barbecue.

319
00:15:48,760 --> 00:15:49,820
Dave, how do you like your steak?

320
00:15:49,820 --> 00:15:52,370
I'm a vampire sir, I like mine pretty bloody.

321
00:15:52,370 --> 00:15:54,430
A man after my own heart.

322
00:15:54,430 --> 00:15:57,100
So Alyson tells us that you're into some

323
00:15:57,940 --> 00:15:59,090
hush hush government villains.

324
00:15:59,090 --> 00:16:00,260
Dad, grill the steak, not Dave.

325
00:16:00,260 --> 00:16:02,210
Just making conversation, princess.

326
00:16:02,210 --> 00:16:03,400
That's all right.

327
00:16:03,400 --> 00:16:05,080
It's his job, he's a dad.

328
00:16:05,080 --> 00:16:05,913
Yes, sir.

329
00:16:07,160 --> 00:16:08,210
All I can tell you is

330
00:16:09,100 --> 00:16:10,060
I'm proud of what I do.

331
00:16:10,060 --> 00:16:10,893
And if you knew more,

332
00:16:10,893 --> 00:16:13,900
you wouldn't think less of me.

333
00:16:13,900 --> 00:16:15,656
Impressive answer.

334
00:16:15,656 --> 00:16:16,656
Well-spoken.

335
00:16:18,332 --> 00:16:20,832
(baby crying)

336
00:16:22,322 --> 00:16:24,190
Okay honey, what's up with you?

337
00:16:24,190 --> 00:16:25,916
What's up with my little nephew?

338
00:16:25,916 --> 00:16:27,470
He lost his balloon in the tree.

339
00:16:27,470 --> 00:16:29,303
Here you are, Grandma's got another balloon

340
00:16:29,303 --> 00:16:30,136
here for you.

341
00:16:30,136 --> 00:16:31,291
Oh look here!
Yeah,

342
00:16:31,291 --> 00:16:32,543
I'm afraid he wants his balloon.

343
00:16:32,543 --> 00:16:34,341
I'm afraid you're right.

344
00:16:34,341 --> 00:16:35,841
Where you going?

345
00:16:54,066 --> 00:16:57,816
(crowd clapping)
Well done!

346
00:16:59,776 --> 00:17:01,026
Look at that.

347
00:17:03,577 --> 00:17:06,053
He's a little bit crazy, but I like him.

348
00:17:07,050 --> 00:17:08,430
He's not crazy, he's

349
00:17:09,270 --> 00:17:10,103
kind of perfect.

350
00:17:16,796 --> 00:17:19,647
(crowd cheering)

351
00:17:19,647 --> 00:17:23,397
(speech drowned by clapping)

352
00:17:25,915 --> 00:17:27,749
What are you thinking?

353
00:17:30,213 --> 00:17:32,473
I was thinking how the past few days,

354
00:17:33,670 --> 00:17:34,870
I've never been happier.

355
00:17:39,230 --> 00:17:40,830
I'm happy, I want to stay happy.

356
00:17:43,420 --> 00:17:44,467
Well, if there's anything I can do to help.

357
00:17:44,467 --> 00:17:45,753
You could marry me.

358
00:17:47,665 --> 00:17:50,248
(gentle music)

359
00:17:54,187 --> 00:17:55,020
Marry me.

360
00:18:16,543 --> 00:18:17,460
I love you.

361
00:18:18,810 --> 00:18:21,320
I know it's not supposed to happen this fast.

362
00:18:21,320 --> 00:18:22,153
But it did.

363
00:18:24,000 --> 00:18:25,473
You too, huh?
Mhmm.

364
00:18:26,670 --> 00:18:27,990
Okay, so let's do it.

365
00:18:27,990 --> 00:18:29,130
Let's get married.

366
00:18:31,430 --> 00:18:32,263
I don't know.

367
00:18:32,263 --> 00:18:34,273
I don't know who I would be marrying.

368
00:18:37,090 --> 00:18:39,790
A man who vanishes and then reappears,

369
00:18:39,790 --> 00:18:40,943
no questions allowed.

370
00:18:42,234 --> 00:18:43,834
I don't think I can handle that.

371
00:18:45,680 --> 00:18:47,350
You won't have to.

372
00:18:47,350 --> 00:18:48,560
My stint is almost over.

373
00:18:48,560 --> 00:18:51,098
I'm going to be a full fledged four-star civilian.

374
00:18:51,098 --> 00:18:52,765
When?
Soon, soon.

375
00:18:54,013 --> 00:18:55,413
And then what will you do?

376
00:18:58,550 --> 00:18:59,770
Come back here, sit on the porch,

377
00:18:59,770 --> 00:19:00,620
get old with you.

378
00:19:13,350 --> 00:19:15,950
Our parajumper training these major's shaping up.

379
00:19:15,950 --> 00:19:17,550
I'm putting you in full charge.

380
00:19:17,550 --> 00:19:19,130
I want you to analyze the weaknesses

381
00:19:19,130 --> 00:19:21,320
and implement any necessary changes.

382
00:19:21,320 --> 00:19:23,740
As always, I trust your judgment.

383
00:19:23,740 --> 00:19:24,970
I've been doing a lot of thinking.

384
00:19:24,970 --> 00:19:27,420
My life, my career.

385
00:19:27,420 --> 00:19:28,930
I'm not sure this is what I'm meant to be doing.

386
00:19:28,930 --> 00:19:30,320
For god's sake, Dave, you're the best there is!

387
00:19:30,320 --> 00:19:32,770
That's reason enough to keep doing it.

388
00:19:32,770 --> 00:19:35,310
I don't want to hear this kind of crap from you again.

389
00:19:35,310 --> 00:19:36,143
No, sir.

390
00:19:37,773 --> 00:19:40,251
(cartoon booming and clapping)

391
00:19:40,251 --> 00:19:42,663
Oh Popeye, I'm scared.

392
00:19:42,663 --> 00:19:45,123
Ain't nothing to be scared about.

393
00:19:47,413 --> 00:19:49,490
(gentle music)

394
00:19:49,490 --> 00:19:52,277
Olive, get back from under the table!

395
00:19:52,277 --> 00:19:54,788
I'm still scared!

396
00:19:54,788 --> 00:19:56,793
Attention, attention everybody,

397
00:19:56,793 --> 00:19:58,876
the virus strikes again!

398
00:20:07,164 --> 00:20:08,377
You need something from the fridge?

399
00:20:08,377 --> 00:20:09,210
Nah.

400
00:20:13,610 --> 00:20:15,918
The boys are wanting a dog.

401
00:20:15,918 --> 00:20:16,868
I said I'd ask you.

402
00:20:19,200 --> 00:20:20,740
Okay, sure.

403
00:20:20,740 --> 00:20:21,573
Good.

404
00:20:23,110 --> 00:20:24,247
Go, tell 'em.

405
00:20:25,272 --> 00:20:26,922
They'll love hearing it from you.

406
00:20:33,661 --> 00:20:36,244
(gentle music)

407
00:21:36,287 --> 00:21:37,713
Going for my ride.

408
00:21:39,260 --> 00:21:40,510
Turn on the sprinklers.

409
00:21:41,510 --> 00:21:42,343
Sure.

410
00:21:54,563 --> 00:21:57,563
(crickets chirping)

411
00:22:18,324 --> 00:22:21,324
(suspenseful music)

412
00:22:58,384 --> 00:23:01,051
(bike clanging)

413
00:23:16,393 --> 00:23:18,893
(tense music)

414
00:23:36,093 --> 00:23:38,926
(water splashing)

415
00:23:42,122 --> 00:23:45,122
(suspenseful music)

416
00:24:43,099 --> 00:24:46,256
(phone ringing)

417
00:24:46,256 --> 00:24:47,089
Yes?

418
00:24:58,065 --> 00:24:59,140
We're going to go over here.

419
00:24:59,140 --> 00:25:00,140
Current's moving pretty swift.

420
00:25:00,140 --> 00:25:01,358
Let's get some boats in now.

421
00:25:01,358 --> 00:25:02,191
Dispatch to unit three,

422
00:25:02,191 --> 00:25:04,785
dispatch to unit three, what's your 20?

423
00:25:04,785 --> 00:25:05,789
This is three,

424
00:25:05,789 --> 00:25:07,397
we're just pulling up on the scene now.

425
00:25:07,397 --> 00:25:09,275
Dispatch due to fire rescue,

426
00:25:09,275 --> 00:25:11,490
we're gonna need some more units out here.

427
00:25:11,490 --> 00:25:13,090
Okay Paul, let's dig in.

428
00:25:14,252 --> 00:25:16,720
Rescue One, this is ground.

429
00:25:16,720 --> 00:25:18,720
Have you got any vision at all up there?

430
00:25:19,640 --> 00:25:22,060
Got nothing at all, Sarge.

431
00:25:22,060 --> 00:25:23,290
I'll hover down to 300 feet,

432
00:25:23,290 --> 00:25:24,480
gonna slide on downstream,

433
00:25:24,480 --> 00:25:26,167
see if I can get any more visual.

434
00:25:26,167 --> 00:25:27,059
It's pretty murky.

435
00:25:27,059 --> 00:25:28,840
Okay if you brake down a little bit lower

436
00:25:28,840 --> 00:25:29,770
and just take a little slower.

437
00:25:29,770 --> 00:25:31,789
Look, we got to find this guy.

438
00:25:31,789 --> 00:25:33,849
10-4.

439
00:25:33,849 --> 00:25:35,665
Yeah, we're sure it's nothing else.

440
00:25:35,665 --> 00:25:38,155
Let's just wait till we hear something.

441
00:25:38,155 --> 00:25:39,738
Okay, okay, okay.

442
00:25:42,933 --> 00:25:47,016
Come on, come on, dig in, boys, let's go.

443
00:25:58,793 --> 00:26:00,853
(Cindy sobbing)

444
00:26:00,853 --> 00:26:02,549
Okay, okay.

445
00:26:02,549 --> 00:26:03,382
Okay.

446
00:26:11,560 --> 00:26:12,755
(thunder rumbling)

447
00:26:12,755 --> 00:26:15,672
(pebbles clanking)

448
00:26:21,198 --> 00:26:23,781
(gentle music)

449
00:26:44,155 --> 00:26:45,738
Mission complete.

450
00:26:56,226 --> 00:26:58,809
(gentle music)

451
00:27:18,538 --> 00:27:20,371
Where's your stuff?

452
00:27:21,960 --> 00:27:23,940
I just showed you my stuff.

453
00:27:23,940 --> 00:27:25,900
Stop it, you know what I mean.

454
00:27:27,650 --> 00:27:32,650
Well, I can't get my gear or my pay till I'm debriefed.

455
00:27:32,720 --> 00:27:34,420
They owe me a huge chunk of back pay

456
00:27:34,420 --> 00:27:35,670
and all my severance, but

457
00:27:37,200 --> 00:27:39,070
I want to see you, so I came here first.

458
00:27:39,070 --> 00:27:40,520
So you're going away again?

459
00:27:42,190 --> 00:27:43,690
No, not till I feel like it.

460
00:27:44,600 --> 00:27:47,600
I told you my stint is over, I can do what I want.

461
00:27:47,600 --> 00:27:49,450
They'll debrief me at my convenience.

462
00:27:50,760 --> 00:27:53,990
So you've got no job,

463
00:27:53,990 --> 00:27:57,542
no money, no home,

464
00:27:57,542 --> 00:27:58,610
and no clothes?

465
00:27:58,610 --> 00:28:00,017
Yeah, yeah, that's about the size of it.

466
00:28:00,017 --> 00:28:01,663
And you did this for me?

467
00:28:02,716 --> 00:28:03,870
I did it for us.

468
00:28:03,870 --> 00:28:06,700
Well, that's what I meant.

469
00:28:06,700 --> 00:28:07,533
Oh boy.

470
00:28:08,740 --> 00:28:11,180
I thought you wanted me if I didn't have to disappear,

471
00:28:11,180 --> 00:28:12,580
if you could know where I am.

472
00:28:12,580 --> 00:28:14,430
I did, I do.

473
00:28:14,430 --> 00:28:15,860
I do.

474
00:28:15,860 --> 00:28:16,693
Okay then.

475
00:28:19,420 --> 00:28:20,253
No regrets?

476
00:28:21,690 --> 00:28:22,563
No regrets.

477
00:28:26,700 --> 00:28:29,500
Alyson, you have got a slew of phone calls to return

478
00:28:29,500 --> 00:28:31,290
and there are clients coming in.

479
00:28:31,290 --> 00:28:32,700
Listen, Tad, anything you can handle,

480
00:28:32,700 --> 00:28:34,860
just handle without me and reschedule everything else.

481
00:28:34,860 --> 00:28:35,760
For this afternoon?

482
00:28:35,760 --> 00:28:37,410
No, I'm not going to come in today.

483
00:28:37,410 --> 00:28:39,420
It's pretty crazy in here, Alyson.

484
00:28:39,420 --> 00:28:40,410
Can't you at least come in?

485
00:28:40,410 --> 00:28:43,110
No, I can't, got it?

486
00:28:43,110 --> 00:28:44,253
Got it.
Okay.

487
00:28:50,800 --> 00:28:51,633
I like that.

488
00:28:53,190 --> 00:28:54,410
That's nice, you'll finally be able

489
00:28:54,410 --> 00:28:55,913
to settle down in one place.

490
00:28:56,770 --> 00:28:59,712
So what are your plans now that you're out of the service?

491
00:28:59,712 --> 00:29:00,836
I don't know.

492
00:29:00,836 --> 00:29:02,340
It's been a while since I've been out there

493
00:29:02,340 --> 00:29:03,240
in the real world.

494
00:29:05,220 --> 00:29:06,743
Well, as I see it,

495
00:29:07,700 --> 00:29:09,730
real estate's on the upswing.

496
00:29:09,730 --> 00:29:13,020
There's good money to be made, buying old houses,

497
00:29:13,020 --> 00:29:15,033
fixing them up and reselling them.

498
00:29:16,410 --> 00:29:18,440
Mama and I renovated a couple of fixer uppers

499
00:29:18,440 --> 00:29:20,310
during the last boom.

500
00:29:20,310 --> 00:29:23,090
We started out just for fun, but

501
00:29:23,090 --> 00:29:25,800
ended up with a tidy profit.

502
00:29:25,800 --> 00:29:27,130
If the idea appeals to you,

503
00:29:27,130 --> 00:29:30,290
you might be able to ride this market while it's strong.

504
00:29:30,290 --> 00:29:32,860
A thing like that, you need to spend money to make money.

505
00:29:32,860 --> 00:29:34,710
I gotta wait for my funds to come in.

506
00:29:36,770 --> 00:29:38,083
Look, Dave.

507
00:29:39,210 --> 00:29:42,820
I got a pretty strong line of credit at the bank.

508
00:29:42,820 --> 00:29:45,420
I could loan you enough to make a real start.

509
00:29:45,420 --> 00:29:47,230
A hundred thousand, say?

510
00:29:47,230 --> 00:29:50,040
You can repay me with your profits or your back pay,

511
00:29:50,040 --> 00:29:51,383
whichever comes in first.

512
00:29:54,337 --> 00:29:58,070
That's incredibly generous, sir.

513
00:29:58,070 --> 00:29:59,740
I love my daughter.

514
00:29:59,740 --> 00:30:00,853
My daughter loves you.

515
00:30:01,830 --> 00:30:04,510
As long as that remains the case,

516
00:30:04,510 --> 00:30:06,210
I want to do right by both of you.

517
00:30:11,550 --> 00:30:13,993
Looks like he went along with daddy's proposal.

518
00:30:17,010 --> 00:30:19,113
He's given up everything for me.

519
00:30:21,020 --> 00:30:21,853
I don't know,

520
00:30:21,853 --> 00:30:25,223
I feel really weird about this.

521
00:30:27,203 --> 00:30:28,278
Honey.

522
00:30:28,278 --> 00:30:30,420
That's a kind of romance most girls dream about.

523
00:30:30,420 --> 00:30:32,273
Mom, I'm not most girls.

524
00:30:33,530 --> 00:30:35,038
Alyson, are you marrying Dave

525
00:30:35,038 --> 00:30:36,250
because you think you got yourself into something

526
00:30:36,250 --> 00:30:37,330
you can't get out of?

527
00:30:37,330 --> 00:30:38,620
No.

528
00:30:38,620 --> 00:30:39,653
I love Dave.

529
00:30:41,800 --> 00:30:43,200
I love what I know about him.

530
00:30:43,200 --> 00:30:46,230
I mean, it's not like I know that much about him.

531
00:30:46,230 --> 00:30:48,230
Daddy and I have been married for 41 years.

532
00:30:48,230 --> 00:30:50,910
We're still learning about each other.

533
00:30:50,910 --> 00:30:52,020
Imagine how dull it would be

534
00:30:52,020 --> 00:30:53,263
if you knew everything there was to know.

535
00:30:53,263 --> 00:30:55,700
When I become a mother, am I going to say stuff like that?

536
00:30:55,700 --> 00:30:56,643
Yes.

537
00:30:56,643 --> 00:30:59,071
(both chuckling)

538
00:30:59,071 --> 00:31:00,400
I've been thinking about something.

539
00:31:00,400 --> 00:31:03,410
It occurred to me that the unit that I was in,

540
00:31:03,410 --> 00:31:04,243
I mean, you know,

541
00:31:04,243 --> 00:31:05,370
we were involved with some

542
00:31:06,310 --> 00:31:07,900
anti-terrorist operations.

543
00:31:07,900 --> 00:31:09,470
We had dealings with drug lords,

544
00:31:09,470 --> 00:31:13,390
people who tend to hold a grudge.

545
00:31:13,390 --> 00:31:14,710
Meaning what?

546
00:31:14,710 --> 00:31:16,550
That our lives are in danger?

547
00:31:16,550 --> 00:31:17,383
No, no.
What?

548
00:31:17,383 --> 00:31:18,340
It's not going to be any ninjas

549
00:31:18,340 --> 00:31:19,970
busting in here in the next five minutes

550
00:31:19,970 --> 00:31:21,197
but I do think that

551
00:31:22,190 --> 00:31:24,790
obscurity is not a bad idea right now.

552
00:31:24,790 --> 00:31:28,870
That's why I want to start using my real last name.

