Kind of stinky.

828
00:45:59,093 --> 00:46:00,743
Hmm, can't argue with that one.

829
00:46:02,223 --> 00:46:03,280
What?

830
00:46:03,280 --> 00:46:05,290
Well, I decided,

831
00:46:05,290 --> 00:46:07,010
well, I thought that we'd move in here,

832
00:46:07,010 --> 00:46:09,133
save on rent while we're renovating.

833
00:46:10,350 --> 00:46:11,500
Just brought the essentials.

834
00:46:11,500 --> 00:46:12,710
Everything else is divided

835
00:46:12,710 --> 00:46:14,580
between Mom and Dad's and Patty's.

836
00:46:14,580 --> 00:46:15,793
So you've been busy.

837
00:46:15,793 --> 00:46:16,626
Mhmm.

838
00:46:18,652 --> 00:46:19,652
So have I.

839
00:46:24,445 --> 00:46:25,620
Oh my!

840
00:46:25,620 --> 00:46:26,453
That's only part of it.

841
00:46:26,453 --> 00:46:28,153
The bastards only gave me a fraction.

842
00:46:28,153 --> 00:46:29,420
Dave!

843
00:46:29,420 --> 00:46:30,743
Come on, give me a hand.

844
00:46:33,110 --> 00:46:34,200
It's wet.

845
00:46:34,200 --> 00:46:35,570
Yeah, tell me about it.

846
00:46:35,570 --> 00:46:37,300
Not only do they short me on the amount,

847
00:46:37,300 --> 00:46:38,930
but when they give me directions where to find it,

848
00:46:38,930 --> 00:46:40,342
I had to take a little swim.

849
00:46:40,342 --> 00:46:41,760
What do you mean find it?

850
00:46:41,760 --> 00:46:42,610
How come they didn't give you a check?

851
00:46:42,610 --> 00:46:43,443
A check?

852
00:46:44,900 --> 00:46:46,130
A check?
Yeah.

853
00:46:46,130 --> 00:46:47,310
Checks can be traced,

854
00:46:47,310 --> 00:46:49,530
bank accounts scrutinized.

855
00:46:49,530 --> 00:46:52,210
This is part of a government that doesn't officially exist.

856
00:46:52,210 --> 00:46:54,570
They give me directions and I follow coordinates.

857
00:46:54,570 --> 00:46:55,963
And what do you know?

858
00:46:55,963 --> 00:46:59,270
It's at the middle of a lake, 20 feet deep.

859
00:46:59,270 --> 00:47:00,850
They send me a little message.

860
00:47:00,850 --> 00:47:03,030
You know, you want to get out the outfit, Dave,

861
00:47:03,030 --> 00:47:03,863
you want to get paid?

862
00:47:03,863 --> 00:47:05,340
Well dive for it, screw ball.

863
00:47:05,340 --> 00:47:07,190
Let's see how good you are, you know?

864
00:47:08,653 --> 00:47:10,380
I'm good enough.

865
00:47:10,380 --> 00:47:13,100
These are the guys that work for our government?

866
00:47:13,100 --> 00:47:13,933
I'm not going to miss them.

867
00:47:13,933 --> 00:47:16,037
At all?

868
00:47:16,037 --> 00:47:16,987
Not a bit.

869
00:47:17,958 --> 00:47:19,070
It feels so unreal.

870
00:47:19,070 --> 00:47:21,520
There's over $40,000 here.

871
00:47:21,520 --> 00:47:22,920
Is that real enough for you?

872
00:47:26,221 --> 00:47:28,860
We're going to pay back dad first, right?

873
00:47:47,888 --> 00:47:49,691
Wait, wait.

874
00:47:49,691 --> 00:47:51,524
Who are you calling?

875
00:47:59,052 --> 00:48:00,635
What are you doing?

876
00:48:05,737 --> 00:48:10,737
You look good in green. (laughing)

877
00:48:19,410 --> 00:48:22,102
Okay folks, straight down there,

878
00:48:22,102 --> 00:48:22,935
walk down left.

879
00:48:22,935 --> 00:48:25,270
I should never have agreed to come here.

880
00:48:28,477 --> 00:48:29,530
I was figuring, you know,

881
00:48:29,530 --> 00:48:32,610
some fast food and a few bucks down a slot machine.

882
00:48:32,610 --> 00:48:33,520
Why bother coming?

883
00:48:33,520 --> 00:48:35,610
Look, most of it went towards paying off your dad

884
00:48:35,610 --> 00:48:36,850
and our creditors.

885
00:48:36,850 --> 00:48:37,720
We got a right to splurge

886
00:48:37,720 --> 00:48:38,820
with the little we got left.

887
00:48:38,820 --> 00:48:41,220
I risked my neck for every dollar of this money.

888
00:48:42,130 --> 00:48:43,780
I'm sorry, you're right.

889
00:48:43,780 --> 00:48:44,613
You're right.

890
00:48:53,220 --> 00:48:54,140
Nice, huh?

891
00:48:55,421 --> 00:48:56,560
I'll tell you what, why don't you sit back,

892
00:48:56,560 --> 00:48:57,792
relax and enjoy this

893
00:48:57,792 --> 00:48:59,330
while I'm going to hit up to the room,

894
00:48:59,330 --> 00:49:00,250
make a couple of business calls.

895
00:49:00,250 --> 00:49:01,083
I got a couple of leads,

896
00:49:01,083 --> 00:49:01,916
but I don't want to lose them

897
00:49:01,916 --> 00:49:03,640
just cause we're on vacation.

898
00:49:03,640 --> 00:49:06,060
Okay, don't be too long now though.

899
00:49:06,060 --> 00:49:07,440
I might get really drunk

900
00:49:07,440 --> 00:49:09,733
and start taking off all my clothes.

901
00:49:10,720 --> 00:49:13,456
Oh, I'll be back in time for that.

902
00:49:13,456 --> 00:49:16,373
(Alyson chuckling)

903
00:49:42,978 --> 00:49:45,895
(crowd chattering)

904
00:49:48,167 --> 00:49:51,334
(lightly tense music)

905
00:49:58,323 --> 00:50:01,240
(crowd chattering)

906
00:50:13,691 --> 00:50:16,002
(dice clattering)

907
00:50:16,002 --> 00:50:17,419
Red, 14 red 14.

908
00:50:20,111 --> 00:50:21,444
Place your bets.

909
00:50:22,836 --> 00:50:25,586
(wheel clicking)

910
00:50:48,258 --> 00:50:49,925
Cash it in.

911
00:51:07,937 --> 00:51:10,854
(glass shattering)

912
00:51:12,372 --> 00:51:13,205
Ah.

913
00:51:17,063 --> 00:51:20,313
It's okay, I'm going to my room anyway.

914
00:51:26,662 --> 00:51:29,745
(dealers chattering)

915
00:52:21,530 --> 00:52:23,123
A secret gambling habit, huh?

916
00:52:24,030 --> 00:52:24,903
What next?

917
00:52:27,460 --> 00:52:28,730
That money was supposed to go towards

918
00:52:28,730 --> 00:52:29,650
paying back dad.
It will.

919
00:52:29,650 --> 00:52:31,340
I couldn't do it then, I couldn't tell you.

920
00:52:31,340 --> 00:52:32,350
What couldn't you tell me?

921
00:52:32,350 --> 00:52:34,590
What lie could-
Listen to me!

922
00:52:34,590 --> 00:52:36,710
You know the world I came from, it's not a game.

923
00:52:36,710 --> 00:52:37,543
What I don't tell you,

924
00:52:37,543 --> 00:52:39,820
I don't tell you because it's dangerous.

925
00:52:39,820 --> 00:52:41,620
They paid me with dirty money, okay?

926
00:52:42,460 --> 00:52:44,920
That's how covert operations are financed.

927
00:52:44,920 --> 00:52:46,960
Confiscated drug money pays for a lot of things

928
00:52:46,960 --> 00:52:47,900
our government has to do.

929
00:52:47,900 --> 00:52:49,060
I'm turning around this money

930
00:52:49,060 --> 00:52:51,780
so there is no risk of your father being tainted in any way.

931
00:52:51,780 --> 00:52:53,660
Now we can stand here and argue about it,

932
00:52:53,660 --> 00:52:54,493
or you can help me.

933
00:52:54,493 --> 00:52:55,730
It really doesn't matter.

934
00:52:55,730 --> 00:52:59,076
But I gotta keep doing this until I'm done.

935
00:52:59,076 --> 00:53:01,909
(trunk slamming)

936
00:53:11,540 --> 00:53:13,490
Let's get a drink first.

937
00:53:13,490 --> 00:53:15,320
I don't want a drink.
Come on.

938
00:53:18,271 --> 00:53:19,937
Ah, thank you.

939
00:53:19,937 --> 00:53:21,180
I think you'd want to keep a clear head

940
00:53:21,180 --> 00:53:22,280
for what you're doing.

941
00:53:24,220 --> 00:53:25,390
You know what, you're right.

942
00:53:25,390 --> 00:53:27,585
Soon as I'm done here we're going home.

943
00:53:27,585 --> 00:53:28,418
Come on.

944
00:53:44,250 --> 00:53:45,083
Damn.

945
00:53:48,517 --> 00:53:51,017
(tense music)

946
00:53:54,141 --> 00:53:55,373
Al?

947
00:53:55,373 --> 00:53:56,980
I'm back, I got the face plates.

948
00:53:56,980 --> 00:53:57,813
Great.

949
00:54:07,340 --> 00:54:08,713
What do you think, you'd buy that?

950
00:54:09,770 --> 00:54:10,840
Nice.

951
00:54:10,840 --> 00:54:11,773
Yeah, it'll work.

952
00:54:46,899 --> 00:54:48,066
You know what?

953
00:54:49,085 --> 00:54:49,918
These are too white.

954
00:54:49,918 --> 00:54:50,751
Should have got off white.

955
00:54:50,751 --> 00:54:52,406
Got to go back to the store.

956
00:54:52,406 --> 00:54:53,356
Do you want me to come along?

957
00:54:53,356 --> 00:54:56,356
No, no, I won't screw it up twice.

958
00:54:59,707 --> 00:55:02,707
(suspenseful music)

959
00:55:28,023 --> 00:55:29,586
That's my boy.

960
00:55:29,586 --> 00:55:30,919
Such a good boy.

961
00:56:34,623 --> 00:56:36,183
Yeah, I got word today.

962
00:56:37,340 --> 00:56:39,000
I can get another chunk of my back pay,

963
00:56:39,000 --> 00:56:40,000
maybe all of it, but

964
00:56:41,460 --> 00:56:43,676
it means taking part in a mission.

965
00:56:43,676 --> 00:56:44,556
What kind of mission?

966
00:56:44,556 --> 00:56:45,980
Well, it's not exactly what I call dangerous,

967
00:56:45,980 --> 00:56:48,560
but it just, it might take a while, that's all.

968
00:56:48,560 --> 00:56:49,990
How long?

969
00:56:49,990 --> 00:56:50,823
Two weeks.

970
00:56:52,540 --> 00:56:53,373
Maybe three.

971
00:56:55,551 --> 00:56:57,390
Do you want your dad paid back in full,

972
00:56:57,390 --> 00:56:58,950
us out of debt, free and clear,

973
00:56:58,950 --> 00:56:59,783
our lives back together?
Yes.

974
00:56:59,783 --> 00:57:01,010
Yes.
Okay then.

975
00:57:01,010 --> 00:57:01,913
Dave, look.

976
00:57:02,750 --> 00:57:03,930
Whatever it is you're doing,

977
00:57:03,930 --> 00:57:06,124
I know you're doing for me, but...

978
00:57:06,124 --> 00:57:06,957
What?

979
00:57:06,957 --> 00:57:09,957
Well, you got to know that you're what matters to me, you.

980
00:57:12,525 --> 00:57:13,410
I don't want anything to happen to you.

981
00:57:13,410 --> 00:57:16,430
What I'm doing, I'm doing for us.

982
00:57:16,430 --> 00:57:17,263
Remember that.

983
00:57:18,100 --> 00:57:18,933
Trust it.

984
00:57:22,509 --> 00:57:25,176
(door knocking)

985
00:57:30,690 --> 00:57:32,290
Hello.

986
00:57:32,290 --> 00:57:33,123
Patty.

987
00:57:33,123 --> 00:57:34,810
I was shopping for myself.

988
00:57:34,810 --> 00:57:36,130
What's one extra bag?

989
00:57:36,130 --> 00:57:38,363
It's not like I'm homeless or anything.

990
00:57:39,270 --> 00:57:40,610
Yeah, but I bet you don't have anything

991
00:57:40,610 --> 00:57:41,860
worth eating around here.

992
00:57:42,950 --> 00:57:44,820
so I got you that lemon chicken

993
00:57:44,820 --> 00:57:47,170
that you liked so much that time you were over.

994
00:57:48,830 --> 00:57:51,770
Well, gee, the place is looking real good.

995
00:57:51,770 --> 00:57:53,070
Real good.

996
00:57:53,070 --> 00:57:54,910
All right, Patty, I know you're dying to ask.

997
00:57:54,910 --> 00:57:56,930
No, I haven't heard from Dave yet.

998
00:57:56,930 --> 00:57:58,600
And I'm, oh,

999
00:57:58,600 --> 00:58:01,120
I'm really beginning to freak out about this.

1000
00:58:01,120 --> 00:58:01,953
Why?

1001
00:58:01,953 --> 00:58:03,151
Well, I do.

1002
00:58:03,151 --> 00:58:06,100
I think he might be involved in something

1003
00:58:06,100 --> 00:58:07,233
really bad.
Really what?

1004
00:58:08,300 --> 00:58:13,300
Rogue CIA, Oliver North kind of thing.

1005
00:58:13,330 --> 00:58:14,403
Well, he might be.

1006
00:58:18,110 --> 00:58:20,040
He might be just more than you think.

1007
00:58:20,040 --> 00:58:21,963
What are you saying?

1008
00:58:21,963 --> 00:58:23,120
Nothing, nothing.

1009
00:58:23,120 --> 00:58:23,953
Patty.

1010
00:58:26,510 --> 00:58:28,090
Jerry made me promise not to tell you.

1011
00:58:28,090 --> 00:58:29,190
So don't tell him I told you.

1012
00:58:29,190 --> 00:58:30,293
Tell me.

1013
00:58:33,420 --> 00:58:37,980
Dave borrowed $20,000 from Jerry

1014
00:58:37,980 --> 00:58:39,800
several months ago

1015
00:58:39,800 --> 00:58:41,670
and he hasn't paid back at dime.

1016
00:58:41,670 --> 00:58:43,770
Why didn't you tell me this?

1017
00:58:43,770 --> 00:58:45,160
Anyway, you know,

1018
00:58:45,160 --> 00:58:49,163
Jerry's sorta considered it a write off at this point.

1019
00:58:50,124 --> 00:58:51,575
Oh, no.

1020
00:58:51,575 --> 00:58:52,694
Take it.

1021
00:58:52,694 --> 00:58:54,495
Go in the back, in the back!

1022
00:58:54,495 --> 00:58:57,669
Clear out, let's go, hurry up.

1023
00:58:57,669 --> 00:58:58,502
Move it!

1024
00:59:00,402 --> 00:59:01,819
I said head down!

1025
00:59:03,024 --> 00:59:04,158
Let's go.

1026
00:59:04,158 --> 00:59:05,494
It's all in there.

1027
00:59:05,494 --> 00:59:06,327
Come on.

1028
00:59:08,914 --> 00:59:11,557
Big bills, nothing under 20.

1029
00:59:11,557 --> 00:59:12,390
Hurry up.

1030
00:59:14,023 --> 00:59:15,453
Hurry up!

1031
00:59:15,453 --> 00:59:16,953
Move it, let's go!

1032
00:59:18,277 --> 00:59:19,777
I said heads down!

1033
00:59:21,141 --> 00:59:22,144
Okay, that's it.

1034
00:59:22,144 --> 00:59:23,332
That's it, all right, bring it to me, come on.

1035
00:59:23,332 --> 00:59:24,249
Right here.

1036
00:59:27,520 --> 00:59:28,353
No please.

1037
00:59:28,353 --> 00:59:29,186
Please, no, no!
On the ground.

1038
00:59:29,186 --> 00:59:30,184
Shut up, don't talk!

1039
00:59:30,184 --> 00:59:31,935
You, you, let's go, come on.

1040
00:59:31,935 --> 00:59:32,908
Get up, follow me in the back.

1041
00:59:32,908 --> 00:59:33,908
You see her?

1042
00:59:35,225 --> 00:59:36,142
Open it up.

1043
00:59:37,727 --> 00:59:38,560
Come on!

1044
00:59:50,880 --> 00:59:52,550
I'd like to get a safety deposit box.

1045
00:59:52,550 --> 00:59:54,190
Are you a customer?

1046
00:59:54,190 --> 00:59:55,660
No, do I have to be?

1047
00:59:55,660 --> 00:59:58,550
No, just fill out this form.

1048
00:59:58,550 --> 00:59:59,383
Thank you.

1049
01:00:03,409 --> 01:00:05,326
Taxi over here.

1050
01:00:07,599 --> 01:00:09,349
Thank you.

1051
01:00:58,997 --> 01:01:02,400
(phone beeping)

1052
01:01:02,400 --> 01:01:04,711
(phone ringing)

1053
01:01:04,711 --> 01:01:05,640
Hello?

1054
01:01:05,640 --> 01:01:06,483
Hey, it's me.

1055
01:01:07,530 --> 01:01:09,130
I need your help with something.

1056
01:01:11,326 --> 01:01:14,409
(chill lounge music)

1057
01:01:19,921 --> 01:01:22,671
Would it bother you if I smoke?

1058
01:01:24,458 --> 01:01:26,523
Well if it did, I shouldn't be in a bar.

1059
01:01:33,830 --> 01:01:34,663
Here, I got it.

1060
01:01:46,050 --> 01:01:46,883
Thanks.

1061
01:01:48,100 --> 01:01:49,430
They booked me into a non smoking room

1062
01:01:49,430 --> 01:01:50,940
then told me I couldn't smoke in the lobby

1063
01:01:50,940 --> 01:01:53,043
and so here I am.

1064
01:01:54,750 --> 01:01:55,583
What about you?

1065
01:01:55,583 --> 01:01:56,793
What about me what?

1066
01:01:57,740 --> 01:01:59,103
Alone in a hotel bar.

1067
01:02:00,780 --> 01:02:02,270
They booked me into a non drinking room?

1068
01:02:02,270 --> 01:02:03,563
I don't know.

1069
01:02:04,650 --> 01:02:06,680
Well, are you here on business?

1070
01:02:06,680 --> 01:02:07,800
No, I'm just passing through.

1071
01:02:07,800 --> 01:02:08,633
What about you?

1072
01:02:08,633 --> 01:02:10,050
I'm a sales rep for clothing line.

1073
01:02:10,050 --> 01:02:11,237
It involves a lot of travel.

1074
01:02:11,237 --> 01:02:12,070
Yeah, you like it?

1075
01:02:12,070 --> 01:02:14,230
Yeah, it's an adventure.

1076
01:02:14,230 --> 01:02:15,610
When you're divorced with no kids,

1077
01:02:15,610 --> 01:02:17,831
adventure's a pretty good trade off.

1078
01:02:17,831 --> 01:02:19,040
Yeah.

1079
01:02:19,040 --> 01:02:20,274
Yeah, I feel that way.

1080
01:02:20,274 --> 01:02:22,000
I have to feel that way for what I do.

1081
01:02:22,000 --> 01:02:23,630
Which is?

1082
01:02:23,630 --> 01:02:24,993
I work for the government.

1083
01:02:26,420 --> 01:02:27,253
What I do is

1084
01:02:29,550 --> 01:02:32,140
secret and dangerous, but I love it.

1085
01:02:32,140 --> 01:02:33,773
I love the action, love the pay.

1086
01:02:35,110 --> 01:02:37,250
Sometimes it's lonely, but like you said,

1087
01:02:37,250 --> 01:02:38,083
it's a tradeoff.

1088
01:02:42,260 --> 01:02:44,813
I have a fully stocked minibar in my room.

1089
01:02:45,730 --> 01:02:48,230
I could give up smoking for the rest of the night.

1090
01:02:53,350 --> 01:02:55,060
I was feeding you a line.

1091
01:02:55,060 --> 01:02:55,893
I'm a jerk.

1092
01:02:57,020 --> 01:03:00,100
A married jerk who fixes old houses

1093
01:03:00,100 --> 01:03:01,433
and loses money doing it.

1094
01:03:03,350 --> 01:03:05,550
Somehow I have a hard time believing that.

1095
01:03:09,202 --> 01:03:10,035
Me too.

1096
01:03:16,063 --> 01:03:17,498
Good night.

1097
01:03:17,498 --> 01:03:18,831
Night.

1098
01:03:29,575 --> 01:03:31,270
I've got to get into my safety deposit box.

1099
01:03:31,270 --> 01:03:33,330
Okay, I'll just need your name and your number.

1100
01:03:33,330 --> 01:03:36,623
Haywood, 3334.

1101
01:03:37,690 --> 01:03:39,343
And just sign right there.

1102
01:03:41,270 --> 01:03:42,103
Thank you.

1103
01:04:09,930 --> 01:04:12,563
You can look at this in the cubicle out there.

1104
01:04:38,535 --> 01:04:39,368
Oh.
Hi.

1105
01:04:40,260 --> 01:04:41,093
Hello.
Hi.

1106
01:04:43,670 --> 01:04:44,940
I'd like to rent a box,

1107
01:04:44,940 --> 01:04:46,529
but I'm not sure what size.

1108
01:04:46,529 --> 01:04:48,510
All right, well, these are the different sizes

1109
01:04:48,510 --> 01:04:50,187
of boxes that we have.

1110
01:04:54,090 --> 01:04:56,913
So what's the difference in price there?

1111
01:05:06,966 --> 01:05:07,904
Oh, thanks.

1112
01:05:07,904 --> 01:05:08,830
Excuse me.

1113
01:05:08,830 --> 01:05:10,430
I seem to have cut my finger

1114
01:05:10,430 --> 01:05:11,650
on the stupid box.

1115
01:05:11,650 --> 01:05:13,233
Oh, sorry.
Yeah.

1116
01:05:14,600 --> 01:05:16,279
We should figure something out there.

1117
01:05:16,279 --> 01:05:17,735
We should wash that.
It's very sharp.

1118
01:05:17,735 --> 01:05:19,080
But you know, let's put your box back first.

1119
01:05:19,080 --> 01:05:20,130
That's a good idea.

1120
01:05:23,753 --> 01:05:24,586
Thanks.

1121
01:05:38,340 --> 01:05:40,470
What is your purpose for entering Mexico?

1122
01:05:40,470 --> 01:05:41,303
Tourist.

1123
01:06:03,045 --> 01:06:05,270
And for how long?

1124
01:06:05,270 --> 01:06:06,770
Till you run out of tequila.

1125
01:06:12,341 --> 01:06:13,174
Vamos.

1126
01:06:22,221 --> 01:06:24,990
(door knocking)

1127
01:06:24,990 --> 01:06:26,140
Okay.

1128
01:06:26,140 --> 01:06:27,610
I went to that old locksmith

1129
01:06:27,610 --> 01:06:28,443
that mom and dad used to go to

1130
01:06:28,443 --> 01:06:30,800
because I figured that he wouldn't be suspicious.

1131
01:06:30,800 --> 01:06:32,740
Well he was, a little, I think.

1132
01:06:32,740 --> 01:06:33,887
Hi.

1133
01:06:33,887 --> 01:06:34,720
But...

1134
01:06:36,529 --> 01:06:37,363
I got it.

1135
01:06:40,069 --> 01:06:41,440
Now be careful this time.

1136
01:06:41,440 --> 01:06:42,273
I know the routine.

1137
01:06:42,273 --> 01:06:43,529
I'll just be a few minutes.

1138
01:07:21,380 --> 01:07:24,547
(lightly tense music)

1139
01:08:09,480 --> 01:08:12,303
Patty, I don't know what's true, what's not true.

1140
01:08:14,320 --> 01:08:16,210
Dave Bay is a name he was born with

1141
01:08:16,210 --> 01:08:18,170
in Illinois to parents that,

1142
01:08:18,170 --> 01:08:20,470
well, he always told me were foster parents,

1143
01:08:20,470 --> 01:08:22,870
which means he made up half the stuff about his childhood.

1144
01:08:22,870 --> 01:08:23,702
So what?

1145
01:08:23,702 --> 01:08:24,550
People do that all the time.

1146
01:08:24,550 --> 01:08:25,520
There's more, there's more.

1147
01:08:25,520 --> 01:08:27,042
The woman in the photograph,

1148
01:08:27,960 --> 01:08:29,622
the foster mother turned mother,

1149
01:08:30,560 --> 01:08:33,729
she was supposed to have died when Dave was in high school.

1150
01:08:33,729 --> 01:08:37,130
But in the photograph, he's already in an Air Force uniform,

1151
01:08:37,130 --> 01:08:39,370
which means that she didn't die when he said.

1152
01:08:39,370 --> 01:08:40,819
Meaning she still might be alive.

1153
01:08:40,819 --> 01:08:41,653
You're getting ahead

1154
01:08:41,653 --> 01:08:42,486
of me here.
No, god,

1155
01:08:42,486 --> 01:08:43,318
you're taking too long.

1156
01:08:43,318 --> 01:08:45,380
Cut to the chase!
I'm trying, okay.

1157
01:08:45,380 --> 01:08:47,559
According to his birth certificate,

1158
01:08:47,559 --> 01:08:49,200
he was born in Rockford, Illinois,

1159
01:08:49,200 --> 01:08:50,170
and the picture was taken

1160
01:08:50,170 --> 01:08:51,870
in front of Rockford Public Library.

1161
01:08:51,870 --> 01:08:55,979
Now, I had remembered that the mother was a librarian

1162
01:08:55,979 --> 01:08:59,290
or something, so I gave it a shot and I called the library.

1163
01:08:59,290 --> 01:09:01,040
You didn't.
Mhmm.

1164
01:09:01,040 --> 01:09:04,930
Carolyn Bay, beloved librarian for 25 years

1165
01:09:04,930 --> 01:09:09,292
is now retired, not deceased and living in Portland.

1166
01:09:10,350 --> 01:09:11,268
Portland?

1167
01:09:12,265 --> 01:09:14,750
So do you think Dave knows?

1168
01:09:14,750 --> 01:09:15,867
Stupid question, of course Dave knows.

1169
01:09:15,867 --> 01:09:17,550
The question is, now that I know,

1170
01:09:17,550 --> 01:09:18,393
what am I going to do about it?

1171
01:09:18,393 --> 01:09:20,962
All right, all right, come on, let's go sit down.

1172
01:09:22,990 --> 01:09:24,940
All right. (clears throat)

1173
01:09:24,940 --> 01:09:27,250
How does Dave's childhood,

1174
01:09:27,250 --> 01:09:30,270
his relationship with his parents, all that stuff,

1175
01:09:30,270 --> 01:09:31,520
how does that affect you?

1176
01:09:33,170 --> 01:09:34,002
Well it doesn't directly, but-

1177
01:09:34,002 --> 01:09:35,725
Then it's none of your business.

1178
01:09:35,725 --> 01:09:37,723
Patty, how can you say that?

1179
01:09:40,059 --> 01:09:41,940
I have accepted Dave

1180
01:09:41,940 --> 01:09:45,930
as a man of mystery who can only tell me certain things.

1181
01:09:45,930 --> 01:09:47,680
But I didn't know he was lying about the things

1182
01:09:47,680 --> 01:09:48,540
he was telling me.

1183
01:09:48,540 --> 01:09:50,053
I mean, what else is a lie?

1184
01:09:51,090 --> 01:09:52,410
I can't trust him.

1185
01:09:52,410 --> 01:09:54,830
He lied about his childhood, that's it.

1186
01:09:54,830 --> 01:09:56,650
So what?

1187
01:09:56,650 --> 01:09:58,770
It's who he grew up to be that matters.

1188
01:09:58,770 --> 01:10:01,020
And he grew up to be

1189
01:10:01,020 --> 01:10:02,857
honored by the President of the United States

1190
01:10:02,857 --> 01:10:05,300
and the prime minister of England.

1191
01:10:05,300 --> 01:10:07,683
Come on, sweetie, you saw the pictures.

1192
01:10:09,520 --> 01:10:12,603
(light somber music)

1193
01:10:26,250 --> 01:10:27,673
Oh my god, the key.

1194
01:10:52,506 --> 01:10:53,339
Hey.

1195
01:10:56,612 --> 01:10:59,210
Uh-oh, you look happy.

1196
01:10:59,210 --> 01:11:00,580
I would have called if I could,

1197
01:11:00,580 --> 01:11:02,059
but where I was is...

1198
01:11:03,230 --> 01:11:05,680
It's over, I'm finished with those guys for good.

1199
01:11:06,600 --> 01:11:07,630
You get your money?

1200
01:11:07,630 --> 01:11:08,490
Oh yeah.

1201
01:11:08,490 --> 01:11:09,823
Yeah, some.

1202
01:11:09,823 --> 01:11:10,770
Enough.

1203
01:11:10,770 --> 01:11:11,920
Come on, I'll show you.

1204
01:11:13,633 --> 01:11:14,733
At least it's not wet.

1205
01:11:15,850 --> 01:11:17,160
I didn't want to go back to Vegas

1206
01:11:17,160 --> 01:11:19,543
so I made other arrangements.

1207
01:11:21,010 --> 01:11:22,150
Come here, I wanna show you.

1208
01:11:22,150 --> 01:11:23,320
What?

1209
01:11:23,320 --> 01:11:24,970
Close your eyes and hold out your hands.

1210
01:11:24,970 --> 01:11:25,803
What now?

1211
01:11:25,803 --> 01:11:27,273
Close your eyes and hold out your hands.

1212
01:11:29,075 --> 01:11:31,575
(bag zipping)

1213
01:11:35,440 --> 01:11:36,273
Okay.

1214
01:11:38,580 --> 01:11:41,383
Mexican gold pesos for $150 each.

1215
01:11:42,710 --> 01:11:44,860
Where did you get this?

1216
01:11:44,860 --> 01:11:46,322
From the unit.

1217
01:11:46,322 --> 01:11:48,871
They insisted they pay me in gold and they did.

1218
01:11:48,871 --> 01:11:49,960
And where did they get it?

1219
01:11:49,960 --> 01:11:51,930
They're very enterprising.

1220
01:11:51,930 --> 01:11:54,050
Now we can pay your dad back in full, get out of debt,

1221
01:11:54,050 --> 01:11:56,050
maybe take a nice little trip somewhere.

1222
01:11:57,170 --> 01:11:58,520
What's your dream vacation?

1223
01:12:00,460 --> 01:12:01,960
I don't believe in dreaming.

1224
01:12:04,720 --> 01:12:06,670
What aren't you saying?

1225
01:12:06,670 --> 01:12:08,500
What aren't you saying?

1226
01:12:08,500 --> 01:12:10,170
What are the things you haven't told me, Dave?

1227
01:12:10,170 --> 01:12:11,490
I want to know.

1228
01:12:11,490 --> 01:12:12,920
I'll tell you.

1229
01:12:12,920 --> 01:12:14,585
I will, when it's safer.

1230
01:12:14,585 --> 01:12:15,590
And when will that be?

1231
01:12:15,590 --> 01:12:17,233
And say from what Dave?

1232
01:12:18,830 --> 01:12:21,780
If you're in some kind of trouble, let me help you.

1233
01:12:21,780 --> 01:12:23,770
You can trust me, you know that, you can.

1234
01:12:23,770 --> 01:12:24,900
I've been trained not to trust.

1235
01:12:24,900 --> 01:12:25,863
Trust equals death.

1236
01:12:34,120 --> 01:12:36,430
It's not easy battling that kind of conditioning,

1237
01:12:36,430 --> 01:12:37,263
but I'll try.

1238
01:12:37,263 --> 01:12:40,113
I want you to trust me so I can trust you.

1239
01:12:43,183 --> 01:12:44,016
Look.

1240
01:12:45,283 --> 01:12:46,116
I'm tired.

1241
01:12:47,023 --> 01:12:48,820
I want to take a shower,

1242
01:12:48,820 --> 01:12:49,653
maybe a nap.

1243
01:12:50,650 --> 01:12:52,300
Why don't you think about dinner?

1244
01:13:15,135 --> 01:13:17,635
(tense music)

1245
01:14:43,398 --> 01:14:44,315
Oh, Alyson.

1246
01:14:52,693 --> 01:14:55,130
It's all right, I'll grab something on the road.

1247
01:14:55,130 --> 01:14:56,059
Where you going?

1248
01:14:56,059 --> 01:14:57,050
I gotta deal with this.

1249
01:14:57,050 --> 01:14:58,113
It might take awhile.

1250
01:14:59,150 --> 01:14:59,983
How long a while?

1251
01:14:59,983 --> 01:15:00,816
A day or two.

1252
01:15:01,890 --> 01:15:02,940
I'll keep you posted.

1253
01:15:05,720 --> 01:15:07,490
I love you, cowboy.

1254
01:15:07,490 --> 01:15:08,823
Dave, what's happening?

1255
01:15:09,870 --> 01:15:10,840
Tell me what's happening.

1256
01:15:10,840 --> 01:15:14,207
I told you.

1257
01:15:14,207 --> 01:15:17,363
You told me nothing, always nothing.

1258
01:15:18,741 --> 01:15:20,691
I want to know what you're doing, Dave.

1259
01:15:21,814 --> 01:15:23,393
Tell me what you're doing.

1260
01:15:25,455 --> 01:15:28,455
I'm going to do what I have to do.

1261
01:15:48,729 --> 01:15:51,312
(car starting)

1262
01:16:00,000 --> 01:16:03,167
(lightly tense music)

1263
01:16:33,489 --> 01:16:36,156
(phone beeping)

1264
01:16:39,210 --> 01:16:40,980
What city please?

1265
01:16:40,980 --> 01:16:42,010
Portland?

1266
01:16:42,010 --> 01:16:45,743
The number for Carolyn Bay, B-A-Y.

1267
01:16:47,010 --> 01:16:48,960
Hold for a moment, please.

1268
01:17:06,344 --> 01:17:09,011
(phone beeping)

1269
01:17:12,400 --> 01:17:13,500
Hello?

1270
01:17:13,500 --> 01:17:15,383
Is this Mrs. Carolyn Bay?

1271
01:17:18,597 --> 01:17:21,180
(gentle music)

1272
01:17:28,867 --> 01:17:31,534
(door knocking)

1273
01:17:42,830 --> 01:17:43,663
Mrs. Bay?

1274
01:17:43,663 --> 01:17:44,496
Yes.

1275
01:17:44,496 --> 01:17:47,460
Hi, my name is Alison Haywood.

1276
01:17:47,460 --> 01:17:49,790
I'm a friend of your son, Dave.

1277
01:17:49,790 --> 01:17:51,750
He's told me so much about you.

1278
01:17:51,750 --> 01:17:54,000
And he's always said when I'm in Portland,

1279
01:17:54,000 --> 01:17:55,600
that I should look you up, so...

1280
01:17:58,809 --> 01:18:00,240
I'm sorry.

1281
01:18:00,240 --> 01:18:02,590
You are Dave's mom, aren't you?

1282
01:18:02,590 --> 01:18:04,920
My dear, why do you keep talking about Dave

1283
01:18:04,920 --> 01:18:06,233
as if he's alive?

1284
01:18:09,040 --> 01:18:09,883
Excuse me?

1285
01:18:12,720 --> 01:18:14,282
Maybe you better come inside.

1286
01:18:16,987 --> 01:18:19,793
As a friend of Dave's, how is it you didn't know?

1287
01:18:20,700 --> 01:18:22,000
Oh.

1288
01:18:22,000 --> 01:18:22,900
Well, I...

1289
01:18:24,670 --> 01:18:27,353
We've been a little out of touch.

1290
01:18:27,353 --> 01:18:28,410
Oh, you poor thing,

1291
01:18:28,410 --> 01:18:31,110
this must be a terrible shock.

1292
01:18:31,110 --> 01:18:33,023
Shock, yes.

1293
01:18:34,300 --> 01:18:36,933
That's when Dave and Cindy met the prime minister.

1294
01:18:39,150 --> 01:18:42,320
You know Cindy, she's doing better now.

1295
01:18:42,320 --> 01:18:45,023
They've been through so much, Cindy and the boys.

1296
01:18:50,017 --> 01:18:53,370
A wife and children.

1297
01:18:53,370 --> 01:18:54,270
You didn't know?

1298
01:18:56,482 --> 01:18:58,282
You can't have known Dave very well.

1299
01:19:00,210 --> 01:19:02,593
Dave was married before I moved to Portland.

1300
01:19:04,190 --> 01:19:06,330
How could you know where I am,

1301
01:19:06,330 --> 01:19:07,740
but not know about his family?

1302
01:19:07,740 --> 01:19:09,373
I'm sorry.

1303
01:19:09,373 --> 01:19:11,050
I'm having a hard time with this.

1304
01:19:11,050 --> 01:19:13,040
I know your voice.

1305
01:19:13,040 --> 01:19:15,610
You called yesterday for my address.

1306
01:19:15,610 --> 01:19:17,677
Who are you, what do you want?

1307
01:19:17,677 --> 01:19:18,677
I'm sorry.

1308
01:19:19,610 --> 01:19:20,443
It's a mistake.

1309
01:19:20,443 --> 01:19:22,070
Just go!
I'm going!

1310
01:19:35,430 --> 01:19:38,873
Sometimes when I'm having a bad dream,

1311
01:19:40,070 --> 01:19:41,653
I can wake myself up.

1312
01:19:44,568 --> 01:19:46,919
I'll be there in the dream and I'll tell myself

1313
01:19:47,809 --> 01:19:49,410
I don't want to be here anymore.

1314
01:19:50,884 --> 01:19:52,053
And then I wake up.

1315
01:19:55,548 --> 01:20:00,548
(sighing) I can't seem to wake myself up from this one.

1316
01:20:03,710 --> 01:20:06,030
Alyson, I think we all have to face the fact

1317
01:20:06,030 --> 01:20:08,780
that this nightmare is not over.

1318
01:20:08,780 --> 01:20:11,130
The question now is what are we going to do about it?

1319
01:20:11,130 --> 01:20:14,309
Well, that's easy, we nail the bastard.

1320
01:20:14,309 --> 01:20:16,520
I said he was crazy that very first day, remember that?

1321
01:20:16,520 --> 01:20:17,670
I said he was crazy.
Mom, you liked him.

1322
01:20:17,670 --> 01:20:18,503
We all liked him.

1323
01:20:18,503 --> 01:20:19,893
The whole world likes Dave.

1324
01:20:20,970 --> 01:20:23,733
That's how he can take you and Jerry.

1325
01:20:27,710 --> 01:20:29,170
And me.

1326
01:20:29,170 --> 01:20:30,670
So what are you going to do?

1327
01:20:31,610 --> 01:20:33,780
Alyson, the guy could be nuts!

1328
01:20:33,780 --> 01:20:34,980
Or dangerous.

1329
01:20:34,980 --> 01:20:36,500
Oh, that's great, coming from you,

1330
01:20:36,500 --> 01:20:38,910
the one who told me that it was none of my business,

1331
01:20:38,910 --> 01:20:39,743
that I should just leave

1332
01:20:39,743 --> 01:20:40,620
it all alone, right?
I was wrong,

1333
01:20:40,620 --> 01:20:41,580
okay?

1334
01:20:41,580 --> 01:20:42,960
Call the cops, call the military,

1335
01:20:42,960 --> 01:20:43,993
call the other wife.

1336
01:20:44,844 --> 01:20:47,412
This creep's got a lot to answer for.

1337
01:20:47,412 --> 01:20:50,470
I think we may see the return of public executions.

1338
01:20:50,470 --> 01:20:53,641
Patty, we're talking about that baby's father.

1339
01:20:53,641 --> 01:20:54,910
Dad.

1340
01:20:54,910 --> 01:20:59,070
We have to think very carefully before we act.

1341
01:20:59,070 --> 01:21:01,640
Because once this genie's let out of the bottle,

1342
01:21:01,640 --> 01:21:03,353
there'll be no putting it back.

1343
01:21:06,008 --> 01:21:09,175
(lightly tense music)

1344
01:22:33,276 --> 01:22:35,528
(boys giggling)

1345
01:22:35,528 --> 01:22:36,458
Hey!

1346
01:22:36,458 --> 01:22:39,327
Okay, boys, it's lunch time, come on!

1347
01:22:39,327 --> 01:22:41,112
Come on, come on, come on.

1348
01:22:41,112 --> 01:22:42,987
I got you, come here.

1349
01:22:42,987 --> 01:22:44,692
I don't wanna go in!

1350
01:22:44,692 --> 01:22:46,118
Dry yourself up, okay?

1351
01:22:46,118 --> 01:22:48,035
Now you too, come here.

1352
01:22:57,059 --> 01:22:58,411
You know what, get in there.

1353
01:22:58,411 --> 01:23:00,265
Wipe your feet up before you go in the door.

1354
01:23:00,265 --> 01:23:01,098
Go on.

1355
01:23:11,049 --> 01:23:12,164
(car starting)

1356
01:23:12,164 --> 01:23:13,691
Get this thing, yes!

1357
01:23:13,691 --> 01:23:16,023
Left, left, left right left.

1358
01:23:17,500 --> 01:23:19,833
Left, left, left right left.

1359
01:23:23,558 --> 01:23:26,725
(helicopter whirring)

1360
01:23:45,110 --> 01:23:46,500
I should've known.

1361
01:23:46,500 --> 01:23:48,390
He was trying to tell me

1362
01:23:48,390 --> 01:23:51,540
a few days before his accident.

1363
01:23:51,540 --> 01:23:52,490
He was feeling trapped,

1364
01:23:52,490 --> 01:23:53,540
he wanted to get out.

1365
01:23:54,636 --> 01:23:56,036
I didn't take him seriously.

1366
01:23:56,940 --> 01:23:58,760
Maybe I could have helped him.

1367
01:23:58,760 --> 01:24:01,963
Dave's a quitter who destroyed lives in the process.

1368
01:24:03,500 --> 01:24:05,710
Let me tell you about this unit.

1369
01:24:05,710 --> 01:24:07,650
We take the finest.

1370
01:24:07,650 --> 01:24:09,970
We put them through the hardest training in the military

1371
01:24:09,970 --> 01:24:12,559
and we produced 200 of the world's best.

1372
01:24:12,559 --> 01:24:16,670
They can go anywhere, do anything for one purpose,

1373
01:24:16,670 --> 01:24:17,940
to save lives.

1374
01:24:17,940 --> 01:24:22,700
All I know is he told me he resigned

1375
01:24:22,700 --> 01:24:24,710
and that he was being debriefed and

1376
01:24:25,809 --> 01:24:28,570
that he was getting his back pay you owed him.

1377
01:24:28,570 --> 01:24:29,403
Owed him?

1378
01:24:30,420 --> 01:24:32,523
We don't owe our men money.

1379
01:24:36,898 --> 01:24:39,610
I was grooming him to take over.

1380
01:24:39,610 --> 01:24:41,210
He had everything going for him.

1381
01:24:42,407 --> 01:24:44,513
I guess he didn't see it that way.

1382
01:24:47,120 --> 01:24:49,720
I can't believe what he put them through.

1383
01:24:49,720 --> 01:24:52,023
His mother, Cindy, the kids.

1384
01:24:53,050 --> 01:24:54,950
I'm on that list somewhere.

1385
01:24:54,950 --> 01:24:56,600
Yeah, sorry, of course.

1386
01:24:56,600 --> 01:24:57,433
So.

1387
01:24:59,740 --> 01:25:01,563
He's run away again.

1388
01:25:02,730 --> 01:25:05,893
Is that it, he's just disappeared?

1389
01:25:06,990 --> 01:25:09,130
Before today, I could have told you

1390
01:25:09,130 --> 01:25:11,510
with absolute certainty how any one of my men

1391
01:25:11,510 --> 01:25:13,559
would have behaved in a given situation,

1392
01:25:13,559 --> 01:25:15,303
but that's all gone to hell now.

1393
01:25:16,780 --> 01:25:18,820
But you were right to come to us with this

1394
01:25:18,820 --> 01:25:20,370
because we're the ones who can deal with it.

1395
01:25:20,370 --> 01:25:22,027
We don't leave our men out there.

1396
01:25:22,027 --> 01:25:24,237
And we always clean up our own garbage.

1397
01:25:24,237 --> 01:25:25,178
Wait a minute, what?

1398
01:25:25,178 --> 01:25:26,011
Wait a minute.

1399
01:25:26,011 --> 01:25:27,707
What are you...

1400
01:25:27,707 --> 01:25:28,540
Are you...

1401
01:25:30,237 --> 01:25:32,373
are you talking about taking him out?

1402
01:25:33,559 --> 01:25:35,830
You've been watching too many movies.

1403
01:25:35,830 --> 01:25:40,690
No, I want Dave to face charges in front of a court martial.

1404
01:25:40,690 --> 01:25:42,340
That's what he would want.

1405
01:25:42,340 --> 01:25:44,850
I'd like to be put in charge of this operation, sir.

1406
01:25:44,850 --> 01:25:45,683
Done.

1407
01:25:45,683 --> 01:25:48,030
I want you to go back to California with Miss...

1408
01:25:48,980 --> 01:25:50,450
Haywood.

1409
01:25:50,450 --> 01:25:51,923
We go by the name of Haywood.

1410
01:25:54,120 --> 01:25:56,313
Mrs. Haywood, yes.

1411
01:25:58,770 --> 01:26:00,330
If Dave does return to California,

1412
01:26:00,330 --> 01:26:01,840
you'd better be ready for him.

1413
01:26:01,840 --> 01:26:04,480
Remember, he taught evading capture.

1414
01:26:04,480 --> 01:26:07,263
So you're going to have to rely on sheer force of numbers.

1415
01:26:12,564 --> 01:26:16,231
(lightly suspenseful music)

1416
01:26:51,610 --> 01:26:52,443
Hello, cowboy.

1417
01:26:54,800 --> 01:26:56,000
Didn't mean to wake you.

1418
01:26:58,570 --> 01:26:59,870
What are you doing here?

1419
01:27:01,494 --> 01:27:02,327
I live here.

1420
01:27:13,520 --> 01:27:14,370
Hey, Christopher.

1421
01:27:15,422 --> 01:27:17,172
How you doing, buddy?

1422
01:27:18,056 --> 01:27:20,723
(baby babbling)

1423
01:27:23,090 --> 01:27:24,210
You miss me?

1424
01:27:24,210 --> 01:27:25,043
Sure.

1425
01:27:27,920 --> 01:27:29,220
You looking for this?

1426
01:27:29,220 --> 01:27:30,150
They must be close by,

1427
01:27:30,150 --> 01:27:31,600
the signal has a short reach.

1428
01:27:32,870 --> 01:27:34,370
Who did they send?

1429
01:27:34,370 --> 01:27:35,452
My old friend, Bill?

1430
01:27:36,390 --> 01:27:37,702
Bill prefers this model.

1431
01:27:44,770 --> 01:27:46,300
You think I'm going to hurt you?

1432
01:27:46,300 --> 01:27:47,513
Oh, you've hurt me already, Dave.

1433
01:27:47,513 --> 01:27:49,470
I loved you, Alyson, still do.

1434
01:27:49,470 --> 01:27:50,980
Always will.

1435
01:27:50,980 --> 01:27:51,813
Why?

1436
01:27:52,870 --> 01:27:54,410
Why did you betray me?

1437
01:27:54,410 --> 01:27:55,423
Betray you?

1438
01:27:56,400 --> 01:27:59,360
You have betrayed everyone who has ever loved you.

1439
01:27:59,360 --> 01:28:00,670
What are you talking about?

1440
01:28:00,670 --> 01:28:02,080
Not you.

1441
01:28:02,080 --> 01:28:02,913
I've never betrayed you.

1442
01:28:02,913 --> 01:28:05,200
Oh I can't believe that you actually believe that.

1443
01:28:05,200 --> 01:28:06,032
I do.

1444
01:28:06,032 --> 01:28:07,890
Well then you're crazier than I thought.

1445
01:28:07,890 --> 01:28:08,723
You could've had it all.

1446
01:28:08,723 --> 01:28:10,300
I just wanted us to be happy.

1447
01:28:10,300 --> 01:28:11,133
Let go of me.

1448
01:28:11,133 --> 01:28:11,966
Just let go!
No, not till you say

1449
01:28:11,966 --> 01:28:12,799
you believe me, please.
Believe?

1450
01:28:12,799 --> 01:28:14,293
What am I supposed to believe, Dave?!

1451
01:28:14,293 --> 01:28:15,126
I love you.

1452
01:28:15,126 --> 01:28:16,373
All of this was because I loved you.

1453
01:28:16,373 --> 01:28:21,373
Loved me? (laughing)

1454
01:28:22,686 --> 01:28:23,769
You loved me?

1455
01:28:28,477 --> 01:28:30,393
What were you thinking?

1456
01:28:33,446 --> 01:28:35,369
What was I thinking?
Yeah.

1457
01:28:35,369 --> 01:28:37,286
What were you thinking?

1458
01:28:45,230 --> 01:28:46,713
I had to be with you.

1459
01:28:48,402 --> 01:28:52,350
You know, someday you can understand that.

1460
01:28:52,350 --> 01:28:55,017
Oh no, I don't think so, Dave.

1461
01:29:10,271 --> 01:29:11,104
No.

1462
01:29:26,971 --> 01:29:28,888
It is Bill, isn't it?

1463
01:29:34,256 --> 01:29:35,520
Good.

1464
01:29:35,520 --> 01:29:38,687
(helicopter whirring)

1465
01:29:41,134 --> 01:29:43,181
Capture One Leader to Capture Ground,

1466
01:29:43,181 --> 01:29:44,248
we are airborne, over.

1467
01:29:44,248 --> 01:29:45,308
Capture One Leader,

1468
01:29:45,308 --> 01:29:46,311
this is Capture Ground,

1469
01:29:46,311 --> 01:29:48,037
could you give me an ETA, sir, over?

1470
01:29:48,037 --> 01:29:50,682
Roger, Capture Ground, ETA is six minutes.

1471
01:29:50,682 --> 01:29:55,140
(speech drowned by helicopter whirring)

1472
01:29:55,140 --> 01:29:56,832
Capture One Leader, this is Capture Three,

1473
01:29:56,832 --> 01:30:00,332
you have a flight of three on the go, sir.

1474
01:30:14,500 --> 01:30:15,523
Tell me one thing.

1475
01:30:18,010 --> 01:30:21,463
The money, the wet cash, the pesos.

1476
01:30:23,721 --> 01:30:24,671
Where'd you get it?

1477
01:30:25,620 --> 01:30:26,473
I robbed banks.

1478
01:30:36,300 --> 01:30:37,423
I robbed banks.

1479
01:30:50,710 --> 01:30:51,590
Do me a favor.

1480
01:30:53,720 --> 01:30:56,220
Tell Chris his dad was a hero once, okay?

1481
01:31:00,966 --> 01:31:03,549
He really was a hero, you know?

1482
01:31:10,023 --> 01:31:12,607
(somber music)

1483
01:31:51,199 --> 01:31:53,490
Master Sergeant David James Bay,

1484
01:31:53,490 --> 01:31:56,800
this is the United States Air Force Military Police.

1485
01:31:56,800 --> 01:31:58,370
You are ordered to surrender

1486
01:31:58,370 --> 01:32:00,853
according to the articles of the uniform code

1487
01:32:00,853 --> 01:32:02,112
of military justice.

1488
01:32:02,112 --> 01:32:05,218
Failure to comply will initiate hostile force

1489
01:32:05,218 --> 01:32:06,468
on your person.

1490
01:32:07,969 --> 01:32:10,552
(somber music)

1491
01:32:25,604 --> 01:32:28,104
(light music)

